# UI Styling & Components

## Component Library
- Always use **shadcn/ui** components for UI elements.
- Import shadcn components from `@/components/ui`.
- If a component is missing, run `npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>` to install it.
- Never write custom UI components if a shadcn/ui equivalent exists.

## Styling
- Use **Tailwind CSS** for all styling.
- Avoid custom CSS classes or inline styles unless absolutely necessary.
- Use the `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` to merge Tailwind classes conditionally.

## Icons
- Use **Lucide React** icons.
- Import icons from `lucide-react`.

## Example

```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"
import { Plus } from "lucide-react"

export function AddItemButton({ className }: { className?: string }) {
  return (
    <Button className={cn("gap-2", className)}>
      <Plus className="h-4 w-4" />
      Add Item
    </Button>
  )
}
```
